      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WATTS UP THE HILL (2) was well fancied when resuming but manners let him down. Showed ability last campaign, winning twice in Victoria. Should strip fitter second-up and draws well so is worth another chance. PRINCESS DU FER (3) delivered with a last-start win by 6.5 metres at this circuit and distance. Draws well enough to make an impact again. TARENTAISE (6) should be at his peak at the fourth run back from a spell and has produced some decent efforts so far this campaign including a placing from a similar draw here two back. ALL RIGHT NOW (1) is a newcomer to the Howard James yard from Queensland. First up for six months but was readied with two nice trials here, winning the latest. Keep safe from the inside draw. Something for the Multiples: ITS ALL RIGHT NOW (1)",
